  "description": "Tax Compliance Transcript Explained: when it’s used, what tax professionals look for, common pitfalls, and next steps.",
  "content": "<section>\n        <h2 id=\"when-used\" class=\"section-heading\">When It’s Used</h2>\n        <p class=\"article-text\">Tax Compliance Transcript Explained is used when you need the IRS’s most relevant view for the question you’re trying to answer. The goal is not “read everything.” The goal is to locate the right document for the right decision.</p>\n        <p class=\"article-text\">Use it to confirm status, verify activity, and support a clean explanation to a client without making them stare at a codes list.</p>\n       </section>\n       <section>\n        <h2 id=\"what-pros-look-for\" class=\"section-heading\">What Professionals Look For</h2>\n        <div class=\"card-glass card-hover p-6 rounded-lg border border-slate-700\">\n        <ul class=\"space-y-2 text-slate-300 text-sm\">\n<li class=\"flex gap-2\"><svg class=\"w-4 h-4 text-purple-300 shrink-0 mt-0.5\" aria-hidden=\"true\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke-width=\"2\"><path stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M20 6 9 17l-5-5\"/></svg><span>Dates that establish a timeline (posted vs effective).</span></li>\n<li class=\"flex gap-2\"><svg class=\"w-4 h-4 text-purple-300 shrink-0 mt-0.5\" aria-hidden=\"true\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke-width=\"2\"><path stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M20 6 9 17l-5-5\"/></svg><span>Hold or notice indicators that explain delays and pauses.</span></li>\n<li class=\"flex gap-2\"><svg class=\"w-4 h-4 text-purple-300 shrink-0 mt-0.5\" aria-hidden=\"true\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke-width=\"2\"><path stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M20 6 9 17l-5-5\"/></svg><span>Refund or balance signals that drive next steps.</span></li>\n<li class=\"flex gap-2\"><svg class=\"w-4 h-4 text-purple-300 shrink-0 mt-0.5\" aria-hidden=\"true\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke-width=\"2\"><path stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M20 6 9 17l-5-5\"/></svg><span>Transactions that change liability (assessments, abatements, credits).</span></li>\n        </ul>\n        </div>\n        <p class=\"article-text mt-4\">Professionals focus on sequencing and context. A single line rarely tells the story. The pattern does.</p>\n       </section>\n       <section>\n        <h2 id=\"common-pitfalls\" class=\"section-heading\">Common Pitfalls</h2>\n        <div class=\"card-glass p-6 rounded-lg border border-slate-700\">\n         <h3 class=\"font-semibold text-white mb-3\">Common pitfalls</h3>\n         <ul class=\"space-y-2 text-slate-300 text-sm\">\n<li class=\"flex gap-2\"><svg class=\"w-4 h-4 text-rose-300 shrink-0 mt-0.5\" aria-hidden=\"true\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke-width=\"2\"><path stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M12 9v4m0 4h.01M10.29 3.86 1.82 18a2 2 0 0 0 1.71 3h16.94a2 2 0 0 0 1.71-3L13.71 3.86a2 2 0 0 0-3.42 0Z\"/></svg><span>Assuming a scary label means final action (many items are “in process”).</span></li>\n<li class=\"flex gap-2\"><svg class=\"w-4 h-4 text-rose-300 shrink-0 mt-0.5\" aria-hidden=\"true\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke-width=\"2\"><path stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M12 9v4m0 4h.01M10.29 3.86 1.82 18a2 2 0 0 0 1.71 3h16.94a2 2 0 0 0 1.71-3L13.71 3.86a2 2 0 0 0-3.42 0Z\"/></svg><span>Confusing posted dates with the date a client cares about.</span></li>\n<li class=\"flex gap-2\"><svg class=\"w-4 h-4 text-rose-300 shrink-0 mt-0.5\" aria-hidden=\"true\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke-width=\"2\"><path stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M12 9v4m0 4h.01M10.29 3.86 1.82 18a2 2 0 0 0 1.71 3h16.94a2 2 0 0 0 1.71-3L13.71 3.86a2 2 0 0 0-3.42 0Z\"/></svg><span>Reading a single code without checking what happened immediately before and after.</span></li>\n<li class=\"flex gap-2\"><svg class=\"w-4 h-4 text-rose-300 shrink-0 mt-0.5\" aria-hidden=\"true\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" stroke-width=\"2\"><path stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" d=\"M12 9v4m0 4h.01M10.29 3.86 1.82 18a2 2 0 0 0 1.71 3h16.94a2 2 0 0 0 1.71-3L13.71 3.86a2 2 0 0 0-3.42 0Z\"/></svg><span>Treating different transcript types as interchangeable.</span></li>\n         </ul>\n        </div>\n        <p class=\"article-text mt-4\">Avoiding these mistakes is mostly about workflow: confirm transcript type, build the timeline, then interpret codes in sequence.</p>\n       </section>\n       <section>\n        <h2 id=\"cta-parser\" class=\"section-heading\">Turn It Into a Client-Ready Report</h2>\n        <p class=\"article-text\">Instead of translating raw transcript lines by hand, generate a structured report that explains what happened, what matters, and what to do next.</p>\n        <div class=\"mt-6\">\n         <a href=\"/#how-it-works\" class=\"btn-primary text-lg inline-flex items-center justify-center\">Parse Transcript Now</a>\n        </div>\n       </section>",
